NUMBER 594
NAME Key'n Anchor, Locksmith's Workshop
*DESCRIPTION_START
This corner of the room is a bit less cluttered than the remainder of the shop.
The three walls are each lined with a short work bench upon which are a large
assortment of fine tools and a vast array of lock mechanisms in various states
of repair or disarray. A few strongboxes, chests and coffers are atop the far
bench, their lids open and locks removed. Many more are stacked beneath the
benches, awaiting repair or purchase. A very short stool sits in front of a 
small, well-worn machine. An iron spiral stairway winds down beneath the shop.
A small manuscript, bound in leather, hangs tacked to a nearby wall.
*DESCRIPTION_END
