NUMBER 600
NAME Pit
*DESCRIPTION_START
Dank and musty, the pit you have dropped into is completely empty. Rough stone
walls, slick with a damp algae, surround you on all sides. The slightest fleck
of sunlight can be seen high above your head, reflected by the chute's metal 
surface. 
*DESCRIPTION_END
ASTRAL
CALL 33
DEEPCAVE
DARKNESS
CHANNEL 3773

IFPREVERB CAST -1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER The walls around you seem to absorb the spell's power and sap away your mana.
ENDIF

IFPREVERB PROJECT -1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER Your mind suddenly becomes clouded as you attempt to focus your mental abilities.
ENDIF

IFPREVERB CONTACT -1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER Your mind suddenly becomes clouded as you attempt to focus your mental abilities.
ENDIF

IFPREVERB GO 1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER Squirming and wriggling, you manage to make your way up the chute and breathe fresh air as you emerge in the front yard of the Key 'n Anchor.
  MOVE 500
  AFFECT 500
  ECHO OTHERS A grassy mound flips up and %n scrambles out of a dark hole.%cThe mound immediately snaps shut.
ENDIF

IFENTRY
 IFVAR ORG = 13
   PLREVENT 30
   CONTPLREVENT
   ECHO PLAYER You seem to recall someone mentioning a hidden lever somewhere down here.
   NEWITEM 2 641 
 ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB PULL 2
  CLEARVERB
  IFVAR DROPPED ! 1
    EQUAL DROPPED 1
    ECHO ALL A rope ladder falls from above.
    NEWITEM 3 335 val2=599
    PLREVENT 15
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO ALL You hear the groan of a wooden mechanism and the rope ladder slowly retracts.
    REMOVEITEM 3
    EQUAL DROPPED 0
  ELSE
    ECHO PLAYER The ladder is already hanging beside you.
 ENDIF
ENDIF  
;
NUMBER 630
NAME Rock Chamber
*DESCRIPTION_START
You find yourself in a broad, rock chamber whose walls and ceiling are lost in 
shadows. A long, rectangular table made of oak takes up the middle of the room.
It is lined on each side by a wooden bench and at either end is a wooden chair.
A rough-hewn passageway has been bored from the rock and leads out of the room.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ASTRAL
CALL 33
DEEPCAVE
FIXED_LIGHT
EXIT N 415
ITEM 0 91
ITEM 1 86
ITEM 2 339
ITEM 3 641
ITEM 4 431 adj1=327
EXTEND 4 set at eye level in one wall
ITEM 5 72 val2=599
ITEM 6 411 
EXTEND 6 embedded into the wall
ITEM 7 1508 adj1=210
EXTEND 7 in the floor
ITEM 8 247 adj1=312

IFPREVERB LOOK 4
  CLEARVERB
  SHOWROOM 599
ENDIF

IFPREVERB PUSH 3   
  CLEARVERB
  IFVAR LEVER ! 1
    EQUAL LEVER 1
    ECHO PLAYER You push the lever and hear the clatter of chains rushing through metal rings.
    ECHO OTHERS %n pushes a lever and you hear the clatter of chains rushing through metal rings.
    AFFECT 599     
    DAMAGEALL CRUSH 500 You hear the rattle of chains above you and look up just in time to see the ceiling slam down on top of you!
  ELSE
    ECHO PLAYER The ceiling has been collapsed already, you must pull it back up.
 ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB PULL 3
  CLEARVERB
  IFVAR LEVER ! 0
    EQUAL LEVER 0 
    ECHO PLAYER You pull on the lever and listen as the mechanism slowly draws the ceiling up.
    ECHO OTHERS %n pulls on a lever and you listen as the mechanism slowly draws the ceiling up.
    EQUAL ROUNDTIME 30
    AFFECT 599 
    ECHO ALL You hear the grinding of gears and chains as the ceiling slowly retracts.
  ELSE
    ECHO PLAYER The ceiling has already been withdrawn.
 ENDIF
ENDIF                        

IFPREVERB KISS 6
  IFITEM 9
    CLEARVERB
    EQUAL BACKW 0
    REMOVEITEM 9
  ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB PUSH 6
  CLEARVERB
  IFVAR BACKW ! 1
    EQUAL BACKW 1
    ECHO PLAYER You place your hands around the cobblestone and give it a light shove.%cThe grinding of stone on stone tears through the room as a hole, equpped with a ladder opens above your head.
    ECHO OTHERS %n places %h hands around the cobblestone and gives it a light shove.%cThe grinding of stone on stone tears through the room as a hole, equipped with a ladder opens above %h head.
    NEWITEM 9 335 val2=2030
    PLREVENT 10
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO ALL With the same grinding noise, the hole closes again.
    REMOVEITEM 9
    EQUAL BACKW 0
  ELSE
    ECHO PLAYER The ladder hole is already open.
 ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB LOOK 9
 IFITEM 9
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You look up the hole to the booth above.
  SHOWROOM 2030
 ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB CLIMB 9
 IFITEM 9
  AFFECT 2030
  ECHO OTHERS A hole opens up in the corner and %n climbs up through it.
 ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB LOOK 7
 CLEARVERB
 ECHO PLAYER You peer down the hole into the pit.
 SHOWROOM 600
ENDIF

IFPREVERB PUSH 8
 CLEARVERB     
  IFVAR BUTTON = 0
   EQUAL BUTTON 1
   ECHO ALL You hear the sound of stone grinding against stone rise from the narrow chute when %n pushes a stone button.
   AFFECT 600
   ECHO ALL The sound of stone grinding against stone rumbles throughout the room and you turn to see a narrow chute angling upwards from the pit.
   NEWITEM 1 1508
  ELSE
   EQUAL BUTTON 0
   ECHO ALL %n depresses the button again and the sound of stone grinding against stone rises from the chute as the exit from the pit is closed.
   AFFECT 600
   ECHO ALL The sound of stone grinding against stone rumbles through the small pit as an ascending chute is sealed shut.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
