NUMBER 642
NAME Somebody's rooftop
*DESCRIPTION_START
The slick slate rooftop slants downward at a sharp angle, threatening to
disrupt your balance and drop you to Broadway ten feet below. A stack
of wooden crates peek up over the ledge of the roof. Easily within reach is 
a side window of an adjacent two-story building. 
*DESCRIPTION_END                                                
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
CALL 33
ASTRAL
ITEM 0 475      
ITEM 1 1507
EXIT ABOVE 2152
IFPREVERB GO 0
 IFVAR ORG = 13
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You finger a secret latch, open the window and climb through into the tiny space between the walls.
  ECHO OTHERS %n opens and quickly climbs through the window, closing it behind %h.
  MOVE 643
  AFFECT 643
   ECHO OTHERS %n climbs in through the window.
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB LOOK 0
 CLEARVERB
 SHOWROOM 643
ENDIF
IFPREVERB LOOK 1
 CLEARVERB
 SHOWROOM 644
ENDIF
IFPREVERB GO 1
 CLEARVERB
 ECHO PLAYER You move to the edge of the roof and carefully climb back down the stack of crates.
 ECHO OTHERS %n carefully moves to the ledge and slowly climbs down the stack of crates.
 MOVE 644
 AFFECT 644
 ECHO OTHERS %n scrambles down the stack of crates.
ENDIF
